SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Interiors", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], certification_type: Certificate.certification_types[:letter_of_conformance], renovation:false)), name: "Thermal Energy Demand Performance"), name: "PURPOSE", display_weight: 1, visible: true, html_text: "<p>To minimize the building energy demand through the establishment of GSAS thermal energy demand performance.</p>")
SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Interiors", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], certification_type: Certificate.certification_types[:letter_of_conformance], renovation:false)), name: "Thermal Energy Demand Performance"), name: "ASSESSMENT PRINCIPLES", display_weight: 2, visible: true, html_text: "<ul><li>The Project will <span>assess</span> GSAS energy performance coefficient of the thermal energy demand (EPCdem) in relation to applicable GSAS benchmark.</li><li>The Project will complete <span>GSAS Energia Suite&trade;</span> for E.1 Thermal Energy Demand Performance to establish the <span>criterion level</span>.</li></ul>")
SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Interiors", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], certification_type: Certificate.certification_types[:letter_of_conformance], renovation:false)), name: "Thermal Energy Demand Performance"), name: "ASSESSMENT", display_weight: 3, visible: true, html_text: "<p>The criterion requires <span>assessing</span> the annual thermal energy demand of the building by calculating the EPC value using <span>GSAS Energia Suite&trade;</span>.The assessment considers the thermal energy demand associated with the external and internal heat gains of the building. </p><p>The external heat gains are generally impacted by the passive design practice, which incorporates the building site, orientation, form, envelope characteristics & properties, and shadings</p><p>The internal heat gains are generally impacted by the transmission gains from ventilation, people, lights, and appliances.</p><p><span>GSAS</span><span> </span><span>Energia</span> <span>Suite&trade;</span> determines for each building type, the energy performance coefficient (EPC<span><sub>use</sub></span>) based on the aspects of the building systems design.</p><p><span>GSAS Energia Suite&trade;</span> determines for each building type, the energy performance coefficient (EPCdem) based on the external and internal heat gains. </p><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><p><span>EPC</span><span><sub>dem</sub></span></p></td><td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><p><span>=</span></p></td><td><p><span>Q</span><span><sub>dem_norm</sub></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span>Q</span><span><sub>dem_ref</sub></span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Where:</p><p>EPC<span><sub>dem</sub></span> \tis the thermal energy demand performance coefficient.</p><p>E<span><sub>use_norm</sub></span> \tis the normalized energy use in kWh/m<span><sup>2</sup></span>/yr.</p><p>Q<span><sub>dem_norm</sub></span> \tis the normalized thermal energy demand in kWh/m<span><sup>2</sup></span>/yr.</p><p>Q<span><sub>dem_ref</sub></span> \tis GSAS benchmark for the thermal energy demand. It is the reference energy of the notional building for a specific building type in kWh/m<span><sup>2</sup></span>/yr.</p><p><br/>The <span>criterion level</span> is established based on the result of the EPC<span><sub>dem</sub></span>.</p>")
